# Approach
* Lets cosider presence of customer at an open hour gives 1 amount of profit, absense gives 1 amount of loss. 
* Now, the problem is to find the hour when the store is in most profitable position. 
* In other words, given a profit curve, need to find out the peak of the curve.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int bestClosingTime(String customers) {
        int maxProfit = 0;
        int profit = 0;
        int hour = 0;

        for(int i=0; i<customers.length(); i++){
            profit = customers.charAt(i)=='Y' ? profit+1 : profit-1;
            if(profit>maxProfit){
                maxProfit = profit;
                hour = i+1;
            }
        }

        return hour;
    }
}
