# Java simple solution, easy to understand.
# Explanation:
First we calculate penalty when we close the shop at zero hour.

- To do this we iterate over the string and whenever we get a 'Y', we increase the penalty by 1, because we already closed the shop at 0th hour, so whenever a customer arrive we get a penalty. Let say we store it in a variable - "currPenalty" .

Now we try to calculate the same for every hour(i.e. index).
- We again iterate over the given string from index 1 till last index.
Now if we close the shop at 1st hour, we know that shop was opened for previous hour i.e.  0th hour and closed after 1 (including 1). Therefore we can use the 'currPenalty' calculated at previous index and adding or removing the penalty for previous index. *(if customer doesnt come, we add the penalty and if customer comes we remove the penalty bcoz the shop was open at previous index)*

_Now we do this for every index meanwhile calculating the minimum penalty and its corresponding index_.


# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int bestClosingTime(String cust) {

        int n = cust.length(), currPenalty = 0, ind = 0, minPenalty;
        //Calculating penalty when shop is closed at 0th hour.
        for(char ch : cust.toCharArray()){
            if(ch == 'Y') currPenalty++;
        }
        minPenalty = currPenalty;
        //Calculating penalty for every index. When we close shop at every hour one by one.
        //Also keeping track of minimum penalty and its index.
        for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++){
            if(cust.charAt(i-1) == 'Y'){
                currPenalty--;
            }
            else currPenalty++;
            if(currPenalty < minPenalty){
                minPenalty = currPenalty;
                ind = i;
            }
        }

        return ind;
    }
}
```

