# Intuition
Create A Suffix Array of penalty to close at each hour and using it find the first hour with minimum penalty.
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
Calcultate the penalty in one go for clossing at `n`.
Then Compute the suffix array:
if `customers[i] == 'Y'` then `+1` 
else `-1`
Get the min element position and return.
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: *`O(n)`*
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: *`O(n)`*
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int bestClosingTime(string customers) {
        int n = customers.size();
        vector<int> suffix(n + 1, 0);
        int penalty = 0;
        for(char ch: customers)
            if(ch == 'N')
                penalty++;
        suffix[n] = penalty;
        for(int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            if(customers[i] == 'N')
                suffix[i] = suffix[i + 1] - 1;
            else
                suffix[i] = suffix[i + 1] + 1;
        }
        return min_element(suffix.begin(), suffix.end()) - suffix.begin();
    }
};
```

