# Approach
The basic approach is to know the penalty beforehand if we dont open the store at all and then increase the hour at which we shut one-by-one and calculate the new penalty, if the current penalty is smaller than previous, then we store the new min. penalty and store its closing hour.
Finally we return the hour at which we incurr least penalty!

please UPVOTE if this helped you!
looking forward to discussions!
cheers!

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
```O(N)``` as we traverse through the string with a single loop

- Space complexity:
```O(1)``` constant space

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int bestClosingTime(string c) {

        int n = c.size(); // c = customers
        int totalY=0; int cntN=0; int cntY=0;
        int penalty=1e8; //initially taking penalty as a large number 
        int hour=0;      // hour = the hour at which we close

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++) if(c[i]=='Y')totalY++; //counting all the Y's (prefix sum logic basically)

        //if closed at 0th hour=> did not open shop at all
        if(penalty > totalY){
            penalty = totalY;
            hour=0; // => 0th hour
        }

        //traversing through the string
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){ 

            if(c[i]=='Y') cntY++; //counting Y's encountered till now
            else if(c[i]=='N') cntN++; //counting N's encountered till now

 //IMP :    val = the penalty if i shut store at the END OF THIS hour i.e (i+1)th hour
            int val = (totalY-cntY) + cntN; //i.e (remamaing Ys) + (Ns till now)

            //if this 'val' penalty is smaller, then we update our min penalty value and closing hour
            if(penalty > val){ 
                penalty = val;
                hour=i+1; //as closing would be index+1 th hour
            }
        }

        return hour;
    }
};
```

