# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Count two seide penalty.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We have to count penalties at every moment of time. We count two side penalties: right and left. A right side penalty is a penalty for opening hours when there are no customers. A left side penalty is a penalty for non-working hours when there are customers. And at each point of time, we calculate the current penalty as the sum of the penalty on the left side and the penalty on the right side, and after that we compare this sum with the previous maximum penalty.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$O(n)$$

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$O(1)$$

# Code
``` C++ []
class Solution {
public:
    int bestClosingTime(string customers) {
        int left_penalty = 0, right_penalty = 0;
        int best_score = INT_MAX, ans;

        for (auto &x: customers) {
            if (customers[&x - &customers[0]] == 'Y')
                right_penalty++;
        }

        for (auto &x: customers) {
            if (right_penalty + left_penalty < best_score) {
                best_score = right_penalty + left_penalty;
                ans = &x - &customers[0];
            }

            if (x == 'Y') {
                right_penalty--;
            } else {
                left_penalty++;
            }
        }

        if (right_penalty + left_penalty < best_score) {
                best_score = right_penalty + left_penalty;
                ans = customers.size();
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
```
