# Intuition
 In this question there we can get penalty only from two reasons
 - For every hour when the shop is open and no customers come
 - For every hour when the shop is closed and customers come

so to count the penalty of ith hour we will consider two things :
 - how many hours no customer come i.e,the count of 'N' till (i-1)th hour
 - how many hours the customer came but the shop was closed i.e, count of 'Y' from jth index to last element

Now we will return minimum indexed penalty element from the string.

# Approach
  - Count the number of Y in the string 
  - for every iteration of the string 
         if character is Y decrease total count of yes by 1.
         if character is N increase count of no by 1
 - return the index of element with least index and minimum penalty.

# Complexity
- Time complexity
  O(N)

- Space complexity:
  O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int bestClosingTime(string c) {
      int p =0; 
      for(int i=0;i<c.size();i++){
             if(c[i]=='Y')p++;
      }
      int no=0;
      int ans =p;
      int in =0;
      for(int i=0;i<c.size();i++){
          if(c[i]=='Y'){
           p--;
          }else{
            no++;
          }
          if(ans>no+p){
            in = i+1;
            ans =no+p;
          }

      }

      return in;


    }
};
```

