# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Let us say the string  = "YYYNY"

Now, a simple question, **what will be the penalty at the 5th hour** (The size of string) => It is simple

**The total no of "N" in the string**, so it means **the count  = 1 at the 5th index..**

What will be the penalty at **4th index**..**it will be 2**, because we encounter a "Y" and **we closed a shop** when we should not have closed it..

What **will be the penalty at 3rd index**,** it will be 1**, because the shop is closed and **customer also did not visit..**

DID YOU SEE THE PATTERN..

WHEN WE START TRAVERSING FROM THE END OF THE ARRAY..

**FIRST CALCULATE THE TOTAL NO OF "N" IN YOUR SRING...AND MAKE I EQUAL TO COUNT..**

**IF WE ENCOUNTER A "Y", WE WILL INCREASE THE COUNT  BY 1**

**IF WE ENCOUNTER A "N", WE WILL DECERASE THE COUNT BY 1..**

Now, at every point we will just **see the count<=max_count**, if it is then we will just upadte the index..

