<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
For everyhour we need to caluclate number of hours that the shop remains open after that hour **(including that hour)** and number of hours the shop is open before that hour.
   - So if X be the 1st number and Y be the 2nd number then the penality if the shop is closed at that hour would be **X+Y**.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Maintain a Prefix array and Suffix array to maintain values of X and Y for every hour.And return the index at which the penality occured is minimum. 

