# Approach
1. First iterate through the customers string to count the number of 'Y' and 'N' customers.
2. Calculate the initial penalty (penal).
3. Set curr to the initial penalty value.
4. Iterate and Update the penalty based on whether the current customer is 'Y' or 'N'.
5. If the updated penalty is smaller than the current minimum penalty:
    =>Update curr to the updated penalty.
    =>Update index to the current index (i).
6. Return the index of minimum penalty

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(N)

- Space complexity:
O(1)

# Please Upvote if you understood it 👍
# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int bestClosingTime(string customers) {
        int index = 0;
        int cuntY = 0, cuntN = 0;

        for(int i = 0; i<customers.size(); i++){
            if(customers[i]=='Y'){
                cuntY++;
            }else{
                cuntN++;
            }
        }
        int penal = cuntY-cuntN;
        int curr = penal;
        for(int i = 1; i<=customers.size(); i++){
            char ch = customers[i-1];
            if(ch == 'Y'){
                penal--;
                if(penal<curr){
                curr = penal;
                index=i;
                }
            }else{
                penal++;
                if(penal<curr){
                    curr = penal;
                    index = i;
                }
            }
        }
        return index;
    }
};
```

